race.comment: Doesn't look like the strongest race and OCTANE REIGN (7) can break the duck. He was okay last time when sent out $2.30 at Yarra Valley having given a good sight at Geelong two back. This won't take much more winning and he can repay the faith. SUNGAZER (8) is a lightly raced 3yo who faded late first up over this track and distance to finish seventh, chasing a good speed there. He should take plenty from that and can improve quickly. KADDARI (9) wasn't beaten all that far at Pakenham last time and that form should translate well to this easier affair. TASSADAR (6) was quickly up in trip at Mornington second up and struggled, she too could be an improver third up. I AM TITAN (1) next best.
